  "skill": {
    "name": "ai-video-generation",
    "description": "Generate AI videos on RunComfy via the `runcomfy` CLI — a smart router across the full video-model catalog: HappyHorse 1.0 (Arena #1, native in-pass audio), Wan-AI Wan 2-7 (open weights, audio-driven lip-sync), ByteDance Seedance v2 / 1-5 / 1-0 (multi-modal cinematic), Kling 3.0 / 2-6, Google Veo 3-1, MiniMax Hailuo 2-3, ByteDance Dreamina 3-0. Covers text-to-video (t2v), image-to-video (i2v), and Veo's video-extend endpoint. The skill picks the right model for the user's intent (Arena-#1 quality, multi-shot character identity, in-pass audio, cinematic motion, fastest path, sub-15s clip, longest duration) and ships each model's documented prompting patterns plus the minimal `runcomfy run` invoke. Triggers on \"generate video\", \"make a video\", \"text to video\", \"t2v\", \"image to video\", \"i2v\", \"animate\", \"AI video\", \"make X move\", \"video from prompt\", \"video from image\", or any explicit ask to produce a video clip from prompt or still.\n",
    "summary": "Generate AI videos via the RunComfy CLI with access to top video models including HappyHorse, Seedance, Kling, Veo, and more",
